The invention is detailed below by the following figures, which are illustrative of an embodiment of the invention.


FIG. 1 shows, in a very simplified representation, a human joint, for example hip joint, with a defect on one joint surface;


FIG. 2 shows the joint from FIG. 1 together with a natural implant used on the defective joint surface;


FIG. 3 shows a tissue carrier formed by a metal screen for producing the natural implant, together with a depression molded in this tissue carrier;


FIG. 4 shows a section corresponding to line I--I of FIG. 3;


FIG. 5 shows a representation like FIG. 4, but with a thin cell carrier material inserted into the depression or cell base and with the patient's own cells growing on this cell base;


FIG. 6 shows, in a simplified representation and in a section, a perfusion chamber for supply of the patient's own cells during the formation of the natural implant; and


FIG. 7 shows, in a very simplified schematic, a splintered bone fracture with an implant which forms a growth bridge.
